alism)\", \"books\": [{\"a\": \"Chomsky\", \"t\": \"Aspects of the Theory of Syntax\", \"n\": \"Standard theory. Historical foundation.\"}, {\"a\": \"Chomsky\", \"t\": \"The Minimalist Program\", \"n\": \"Current framework. Very hard.\"}, {\"a\": \"Adger\", \"t\": \"Core Syntax: A Minimalist Approach\", \"n\": \"Best pedagogical minimalism text.\"}]}, {\"id\": \"formsem\", \"d\": \"ling\", \"col\": 13, \"row\": 4, \"l\": \"Formal semantics\", \"books\": [{\"a\": \"Heim & Kratzer\", \"t\": \"Semantics in Generative Grammar\", \"n\": \"The standard rigorous text.\"}, {\"a\": \"von Fintel & Heim\", \"t\": \"Intensional Semantics (MIT notes, free)\", \"n\": \"Very rigorous extension.\"}, {\"a\": \"Montague\", \"t\": \"Formal Philosophy (Thomason ed.)\", \"n\": \"Original Montague grammar papers.\"}]}, {\"id\": \"pragma\", \"d\": \"ling\", \"col\": 12, \"row\": 5, \"l\": \"Pragmatics\", \"books\": [{\"a\": \"Levinson\", \"t\": \"Pragmatics\", \"n\": \"The standard comprehensive text.\"}, {\"a\": \"Grice\", \"t\": \"Studies in the Way of Words\", \"n\": \"Implicature. Primary source \\u2014 read in full.\"}, {\"a\": \"Sperber & Wilson\", \"t\": \"Relevance: Communication and Cognition\", \"n\": \"Relevance theory. Major alternative framework.\"}]}, {\"id\": \"histling\", \"d\": \"ling\", \"col\": 12, \"row\": 3, \"l\": \"Historical linguistics\", \"books\": [{\"a\": \"Campbell\", \"t\": \"Historical Linguistics: An Introduction\", \"n\": \"Best modern introduction.\"}, {\"a\": \"Fortson\", \"t\": \"Indo-European Language and Culture\", \"n\": \"IE reconstruction \\u2014 rigorous and detailed.\"}, {\"a\": \"Meier-Br\\u00fcgger\", \"t\": \"Indo-European Linguistics\", \"n\": \"The scholarly reference on PIE.\"}]}, {\"id\": \"typol\", \"d\": \"ling\", \"col\": 13, \"row\": 2, \"l\": \"Typological linguistics\", \"books\": [{\"a\": \"Croft\", \"t\": \"Typology and Universals\", \"n\": \"The standard typology text.\"}, {\"a\": \"Whaley\", \"t\": \"Introduction to Typology\", \